Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:02.02,English,,0,0,0,,Today we start the Odyssey.\N{\rChinese}今天我们开始《奥德赛》
Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.38,0:00:05.96,English,,0,0,0,,And the Odyssey is a sequel to the Iliad.\N{\rChinese}《奥德赛》是《伊利亚特》的续集
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.30,0:00:08.24,English,,0,0,0,,And it's a family story.\N{\rChinese}这是一段家族故事
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.44,0:00:10.42,English,,0,0,0,,It's a story about a homecoming.\N{\rChinese}它是一段归乡的故事
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.60,0:00:11.82,English,,0,0,0,,There are three main characters.\N{\rChinese}有三位主角
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.06,0:00:14.42,English,,0,0,0,,There's Odysseus.\N{\rChinese}有奥德修斯
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.72,0:00:19.64,English,,0,0,0,,Sorry. Odysseus.\N{\rChinese}抱歉。奥德修斯。
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.18,0:00:22.42,English,,0,0,0,,Who is the main character.\N{\rChinese}他是主角。
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.76,0:00:24.82,English,,0,0,0,,And it's called the Odyssey.\N{\rChinese}它叫《奥德赛》。
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.74,0:00:29.26,English,,0,0,0,,Then there is Penelope.\N{\rChinese}然后是佩妮洛普。
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.00,0:00:32.06,English,,0,0,0,,Who is his wife.\N{\rChinese}她是他的妻子。
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.14,0:00:34.20,English,,0,0,0,,And there's Tanakas. Who\N{\rChinese}还有塔纳卡斯。
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.20,0:00:37.70,English,,0,0,0,,is their son.\N{\rChinese}是他们的儿子。
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.62,0:00:44.30,English,,0,0,0,,And as we discussed when we read the Iliad.\N{\rChinese}正如我们在读《伊利亚特》时讨论的那样。
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.70,0:00:49.20,English,,0,0,0,,Homer is first and foremost concerned about the human condition.\N{\rChinese}荷马首先关注的是人类的状态。
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.50,0:00:52.08,English,,0,0,0,,What does it mean to be human?\N{\rChinese}是什么才是人类的意义？
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.00,0:00:57.60,English,,0,0,0,,What does it mean to live in a world of war,\N{\rChinese}在战争、创伤、悲剧的世界里生活是什么样子？
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.82,0:00:59.84,English,,0,0,0,,of trauma, of tragedy?\N{\rChinese}……
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.00,0:01:03.94,English,,0,0,0,,And how can we overcome this adversity?\N{\rChinese}那我们怎样才能克服这段艰难？
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.34,0:01:10.94,English,,0,0,0,,So the Odyssey is about three individuals\N{\rChinese}于是《奥德赛》讲述的是三个人和一个家族。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.94,0:01:13.74,English,,0,0,0,,and a family. And they are all traumatized.\N{\rChinese}他们都已被创伤所累。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.98,0:01:15.96,English,,0,0,0,,And they're all heartbroken.\N{\rChinese}他们都心碎了。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.60,0:01:22.28,English,,0,0,0,,Okay. So Odysseus is trying to return home from the war.\N{\rChinese}好的。于是奥德修斯正试图从战争中归家。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.06,0:01:27.16,English,,0,0,0,,And his problem is that he has PTSD.\N{\rChinese}他的难题是他患有创伤后应激障碍。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.00,0:01:32.12,English,,0,0,0,,Which is post -traumatic stress disorder.\N{\rChinese}这就是创伤后应激障碍。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.34,0:01:35.56,English,,0,0,0,,And this is very common for soldiers who return from war.\N{\rChinese}这在从战场归来的士兵中非常常见。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.84,0:01:37.26,English,,0,0,0,,They've seen so much violence.\N{\rChinese}他们见证了如此多的暴力。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.50,0:01:39.62,English,,0,0,0,,They've seen so much tragedy.\N{\rChinese}他们见证了如此多的悲剧。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.80,0:01:41.42,English,,0,0,0,,They've seen so much senseless death.\N{\rChinese}他们见证了如此多的无意义死亡。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.64,0:01:43.90,English,,0,0,0,,That their souls are shattered.\N{\rChinese}于是他们的灵魂被打碎。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.10,0:01:45.90,English,,0,0,0,,And that is Odysseus' problem.\N{\rChinese}那就是奥德修斯的问题。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.60,0:01:49.16,English,,0,0,0,,Then you have Penelope. Who is suffering from depression.\N{\rChinese}然后你有佩妮洛普。她正经历抑郁。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.06,0:01:51.26,English,,0,0,0,,And why is she depressed?\N{\rChinese}她为什么会抑郁呢？
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.98,0:01:55.36,English,,0,0,0,,Because her husband has been away for 20 years.\N{\rChinese}因为她的丈夫已经离家20年。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.84,0:01:59.18,English,,0,0,0,,And she doesn't know if he's alive.\N{\rChinese}而她不知道他是活着还是去世。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.18,0:02:01.32,English,,0,0,0,,Or he's dead.\N{\rChinese}或者他已经去世。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.20,0:02:03.68,English,,0,0,0,,He's probably dead.\N{\rChinese}他大概已经去世。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.96,0:02:07.60,English,,0,0,0,,Right? It's been 20 years. There's been no sign of him for the past 20 years.\N{\rChinese}对吧？已经20年了，过去20年没见过他。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.92,0:02:11.44,English,,0,0,0,,But she cannot bring herself to admitting\N{\rChinese}但她还是提不出来。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.44,0:02:14.38,English,,0,0,0,,that he's dead.\N{\rChinese}他已经去世。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.54,0:02:18.10,English,,0,0,0,,So she's put herself in a very precarious situation.\N{\rChinese}于是她把自己置于非常不稳定的境地。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.92,0:02:22.82,English,,0,0,0,,There's dozens of suitors who want her hand in marriage.\N{\rChinese}有数十位求婚者想娶她为妻。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.36,0:02:26.02,English,,0,0,0,,And she wants to say no.\N{\rChinese}她想说不。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.70,0:02:28.84,English,,0,0,0,,But she's afraid that...\N{\rChinese}但她怕……
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.84,0:02:30.70,English,,0,0,0,,If she does that...\N{\rChinese}如果她这么做……
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.70,0:02:33.82,English,,0,0,0,,Then she'll be alone for the rest of her life.\N{\rChinese}然后她余生将独自一人。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.00,0:02:35.24,English,,0,0,0,,But she doesn't want to say yes.\N{\rChinese}但她不想说是。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.38,0:02:38.92,English,,0,0,0,,Because she refuses to admit\N{\rChinese}因为她不愿承认。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.92,0:02:42.88,English,,0,0,0,,that her husband, the love of her life, Odysseus, is dead.\N{\rChinese}她丈夫——她一生的挚爱奥德修斯已去世。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.22,0:02:47.84,English,,0,0,0,,In her heart, she feels that he's still alive.\N{\rChinese}在她心里，她觉得他仍然活着。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.28,0:02:51.80,English,,0,0,0,,But in her head, she cannot justify it.\N{\rChinese}但在她脑中，却说不出来。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.84,0:02:53.68,English,,0,0,0,,She cannot explain it. It's just a feeling in her.\N{\rChinese}她说不出来，只是心里有种感觉。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.08,0:02:58.38,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? And so her response, and this is what we call cognitive dissonance.\N{\rChinese}好吧？于是她的反应，就是我们说的认知失调。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.78,0:03:04.18,English,,0,0,0,,Her response is just to shut down.\N{\rChinese}她的反应就是关掉它。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.66,0:03:07.72,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? She just spends all her time alone in her room.\N{\rChinese}好的？她把所有时间都花在自己的房间里。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.42,0:03:10.04,English,,0,0,0,,At first she's weaving stuff.\N{\rChinese}起初她在编织东西。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.20,0:03:12.12,English,,0,0,0,,But then she just sits in her room.\N{\rChinese}随后她就坐在房间里。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.62,0:03:15.34,English,,0,0,0,,Right? And then there's Tammacus.\N{\rChinese}对吧？然后出现了塔马库斯。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.18,0:03:19.18,English,,0,0,0,,Tammacus, his problem is that\N{\rChinese}塔马库斯，他的问题是……
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.18,0:03:23.92,English,,0,0,0,,he doesn't know if his father is dead or alive.\N{\rChinese}他不知道父亲是死了还是活着。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.58,0:03:26.74,English,,0,0,0,,But the man is a legend.\N{\rChinese}但这人是传说中的英雄。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.06,0:03:28.82,English,,0,0,0,,This is a man who won the trophy.\N{\rChinese}这位英雄赢得了奖杯。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.82,0:03:32.68,English,,0,0,0,,And he won the trophy because he won the Trojan War by coming up with a stratagem of a Trojan horse.\N{\rChinese}他之所以赢得奖杯，是因为他用木马计策赢得了特洛伊之战。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.12,0:03:35.62,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So he is a legend in this world.\N{\rChinese}好的？所以他在这个世界里是传说中的人物。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.74,0:03:37.38,English,,0,0,0,,And everyone sings his praises.\N{\rChinese}大家都在歌颂他的赞歌。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.86,0:03:41.54,English,,0,0,0,,And he's his son so he's living in his shadow.\N{\rChinese}他是他的儿子，所以住在他的影子里。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.70,0:03:44.02,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? And\N{\rChinese}好吧？然后
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.02,0:03:48.38,English,,0,0,0,,he wants to prove he's better than his father.\N{\rChinese}他想证明自己比父亲更好。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.84,0:03:51.14,English,,0,0,0,,He wants to become a hero himself.\N{\rChinese}他想自己成为英雄。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.76,0:03:56.80,English,,0,0,0,,But he's being burdened by the legacy of his father.\N{\rChinese}但他背负着父亲的遗产。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.80,0:03:58.92,English,,0,0,0,,The other issue is that\N{\rChinese}另外一个问题是……
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.92,0:04:01.08,English,,0,0,0,,unless his father is dead,\N{\rChinese}除非父亲已去世，
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.36,0:04:04.18,English,,0,0,0,,he cannot inherit his father's legacy, right?\N{\rChinese}他能继承父亲的遗产吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.40,0:04:05.32,English,,0,0,0,,His property,\N{\rChinese}他的财产，
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.18,0:04:10.86,English,,0,0,0,,the reputation cannot be transferred to him.\N{\rChinese}声誉也能传给他。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.06,0:04:15.36,English,,0,0,0,,Then there's his mother who's just sitting around the house every single day.\N{\rChinese}然后还有他的母亲，整天坐在屋里。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.92,0:04:18.80,English,,0,0,0,,If she were to get married, she would leave\N{\rChinese}如果她结婚，她就会离开，
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.80,0:04:21.60,English,,0,0,0,,and then he could be master of his own house, right?\N{\rChinese}然后他就能掌管自己的屋子，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.08,0:04:24.66,English,,0,0,0,,But she's still around, so he's kind of stuck.\N{\rChinese}但她还在， 他有点卡住了。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.66,0:04:28.92,English,,0,0,0,,At the same time, the suitors are waiting for Pernopi's answer,\N{\rChinese}与此同时，求婚者们正等待佩尔波尼的答复，
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.22,0:04:32.02,English,,0,0,0,,which is never going to come. So they're just in the house and\N{\rChinese}答案永远不会到来。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.02,0:04:35.88,English,,0,0,0,,they're eating up all his wealth.\N{\rChinese}他们把他的财富吃光了。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.90,0:04:41.40,English,,0,0,0,,So he is just seeing his life wither away and there's nothing he can do about it.\N{\rChinese}于是他只看到自己的生命在枯萎，自己却无能为之。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.06,0:04:43.58,English,,0,0,0,,All right? So\N{\rChinese}好了？
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.58,0:04:48.28,English,,0,0,0,,he is just depressed as well\N{\rChinese}他也正沮丧着
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.28,0:04:52.94,English,,0,0,0,,and he's angry. But all these things are the same thing.\N{\rChinese}他又愤怒。可这些事都一样。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.02,0:04:55.60,English,,0,0,0,,It's really one. It's really one of cognitive dissonance.\N{\rChinese}这真是一件事。真是一种认知失调。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.76,0:04:57.44,English,,0,0,0,,It's really one of depression.\N{\rChinese}它真是一种抑郁。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.76,0:04:58.98,English,,0,0,0,,It's really one of trauma.\N{\rChinese}它真是一种创伤。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.90,0:05:04.78,English,,0,0,0,,All right? So there's another way we can analyze what's going on\N{\rChinese}好了？所以我们还有另一种方式来分析正在发生的事。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.78,0:05:08.02,English,,0,0,0,,and to think about the soul. And\N{\rChinese}并且思考灵魂。且
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.02,0:05:09.50,English,,0,0,0,,the soul is something that\N{\rChinese}灵魂是个事物
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.50,0:05:13.54,English,,0,0,0,,the ancients were really concerned about\N{\rChinese}古人确实关心此事
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.54,0:05:18.38,English,,0,0,0,,because it was really the most fundamental issue of what it means to be a human being.\N{\rChinese}因为它确实是人类存在意义的最根本问题。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.56,0:05:21.32,English,,0,0,0,,It's something that we don't talk about today, something that\N{\rChinese}它是我们今天不谈论的事物，亦是我们今天不思考的事物，因我们生活在一个物质科学的世界里。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.32,0:05:23.90,English,,0,0,0,,we don't think about today, because we live in a world.\N{\rChinese}我们今天不思考的事物，因我们生活在一个物质科学的世界里。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.90,0:05:27.04,English,,0,0,0,,We live in a world of material science. If we can't see it, it doesn't exist.\N{\rChinese}我们生活在一个物质科学的世界里。如果我们看不见它，它就不存在。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.42,0:05:29.88,English,,0,0,0,,But for most of humanity,\N{\rChinese}但对大多数人类而言，
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.42,0:05:32.52,English,,0,0,0,,sorry, for most of human history,\N{\rChinese}抱歉，对大多数人类历史而言，
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.72,0:05:36.22,English,,0,0,0,,humanity has understood the soul as very present\N{\rChinese}人类把灵魂理解为极其存在的事物
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.22,0:05:40.76,English,,0,0,0,,and as very real and the most significant thing in our lives.\N{\rChinese}并且认为它是我们生命中最重要的事物
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.92,0:05:43.32,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So the soul that they understood,\N{\rChinese}好的？所以他们所理解的灵魂
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.92,0:05:46.58,English,,0,0,0,,let's talk about their understanding of the soul.\N{\rChinese}我们来聊聊他们对灵魂的理解。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.72,0:05:48.56,English,,0,0,0,,And this is true for actually a lot of cultures.\N{\rChinese}这在很多文化中都成立。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.22,0:05:53.06,English,,0,0,0,,First of all, soul is a very complex thing.\N{\rChinese}首先，灵魂是个非常复杂的东西。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.80,0:05:55.96,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? It is almost infinite dimensions.\N{\rChinese}好的？它几乎是无限维度。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.98,0:06:00.66,English,,0,0,0,,The different layers to the soul.\N{\rChinese}灵魂的不同层次。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.88,0:06:04.18,English,,0,0,0,,And there's really a part of the soul\N{\rChinese}灵魂中确实有一部分。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.18,0:06:06.02,English,,0,0,0,,that is you.\N{\rChinese}那就是你。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.20,0:06:09.34,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? That's just you, the person.\N{\rChinese}好？那就是你本人。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.92,0:06:11.18,English,,0,0,0,,But who\N{\rChinese}但谁是呢。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.18,0:06:17.16,English,,0,0,0,,you are as a person is ultimately influenced by other influences as well,\N{\rChinese}你作为一个人最终也会受到其他影响的作用，
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.26,0:06:18.60,English,,0,0,0,,by other factors as well.\N{\rChinese}同样也会受到其他因素的影响，
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.70,0:06:23.42,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So these influences include your family.\N{\rChinese}好的？这些影响包括你的家庭。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.90,0:06:26.24,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? Your culture,\N{\rChinese}好的？你的文化，
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.36,0:06:30.04,English,,0,0,0,,the history, and\N{\rChinese}历史，
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.04,0:06:31.70,English,,0,0,0,,maybe the gods.\N{\rChinese}也许是神。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.88,0:06:34.68,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So again, they're infinite dimensions and\N{\rChinese}好的？所以再次，它们是无限维度，且…
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.68,0:06:37.84,English,,0,0,0,,these dimensions have an impact on you.\N{\rChinese}这些维度对你有影响。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.42,0:06:43.22,English,,0,0,0,,And maybe when you die, maybe there's a part of you that lives on.\N{\rChinese}也许当你死后，或许有一部分你继续存在。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.46,0:06:45.22,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? But there's also parts of you that\N{\rChinese}好的？但还有你的一部分也会回流到宇宙的不同流中。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.22,0:06:50.56,English,,0,0,0,,flows back into these different streams of the universe.\N{\rChinese}好的？所以它是一件非常复杂的事。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.06,0:06:52.88,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So it's a very complex thing.\N{\rChinese}好的？现在灵魂，……
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.74,0:06:56.00,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? Now the soul,\N{\rChinese}好的？现在灵魂，
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.42,0:06:59.06,English,,0,0,0,,another name for the soul that we use today,\N{\rChinese}另一个我们今天使用的灵魂名称，
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.46,0:07:01.50,English,,0,0,0,,if you go to psychology class,\N{\rChinese}如果你去上心理学课，
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.94,0:07:04.46,English,,0,0,0,,their name for the soul is the worldview.\N{\rChinese}他们把灵魂称作世界观。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.74,0:07:09.94,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So\N{\rChinese}好吧？所以
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.94,0:07:15.60,English,,0,0,0,,we have a much more simplistic understanding of our psychology than the ancients.\N{\rChinese}我们对心理的理解比古人更简单。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.82,0:07:18.84,English,,0,0,0,,The idea of the worldview is just our understanding of who\N{\rChinese}世界观的概念就是我们对自己是谁、来自何处以及在宇宙中的位置的理解。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.84,0:07:23.22,English,,0,0,0,,we are, where we came from, and our place in the universe.\N{\rChinese}好吧？我们认为它来自我们的记忆。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.30,0:07:27.00,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? And we believe it comes from our memories\N{\rChinese}Okay? And we believe itcomes from our memories
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.00,0:07:29.80,English,,0,0,0,,and our experiences.\N{\rChinese}和我们的经历。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.66,0:07:36.88,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? And the worldview is important\N{\rChinese}好吧？而世界观很重要
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.88,0:07:39.82,English,,0,0,0,,because it allows us\N{\rChinese}因为它让我们
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.82,0:07:42.14,English,,0,0,0,,and ourselves, this is important\N{\rChinese}并且自己，这很重要
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.65,0:07:45.02,English,,0,0,0,,for things such as planning.\N{\rChinese}像规划之类的事
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.48,0:07:47.72,English,,0,0,0,,Right? Only if you know who\N{\rChinese}对吧？只有你知道谁
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.72,0:07:50.72,English,,0,0,0,,you are can you actually plan ahead because\N{\rChinese}你能提前计划吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.72,0:07:53.30,English,,0,0,0,,then you know what you want to do, what you want to accomplish.\N{\rChinese}然后你就知道自己想做什么，想完成什么。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.30,0:07:57.36,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? It allows for empathy,\N{\rChinese}好吧？它让你产生共情。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.68,0:08:00.96,English,,0,0,0,,building relationships with others.\N{\rChinese}建立与他人的关系。
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.44,0:08:04.32,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? And it allows for judgment.\N{\rChinese}好吧？并且它让你产生判断。
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.66,0:08:09.44,English,,0,0,0,,Basically, what's good, what's bad.\N{\rChinese}基本上，什么好，什么坏。
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.60,0:08:10.86,English,,0,0,0,,What do you like? What don't you like? Okay?\N{\rChinese}你喜欢什么？你不喜欢什么？
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.44,0:08:15.82,English,,0,0,0,,So the worldview and the soul are fundamental to who we are.\N{\rChinese}于是，世界观与灵魂是我们身份的根本。
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.12,0:08:21.16,English,,0,0,0,,Now, in psychology, what they will teach you is\N{\rChinese}现在，在心理学里，他们会教给你的是
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.16,0:08:23.28,English,,0,0,0,,that trauma is not a physical thing.\N{\rChinese}那种创伤不是物理事物。
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.90,0:08:27.14,English,,0,0,0,,Trauma splinters the worldview.\N{\rChinese}创伤把世界观撕裂。
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.48,0:08:30.30,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? There's something about your experience\N{\rChinese}好的？关于你的经历有件事是你身份的根本。
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.30,0:08:33.72,English,,0,0,0,,that is fundamental to your identity,\N{\rChinese}that is fundamental to your identity,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.94,0:08:36.98,English,,0,0,0,,but because it is\N{\rChinese}但因为它是
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.98,0:08:38.56,English,,0,0,0,,so painful,\N{\rChinese}如此痛苦，
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.64,0:08:42.06,English,,0,0,0,,you forget about it or you refuse to see it.\N{\rChinese}你忘记它或拒绝看到它。
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.12,0:08:46.76,English,,0,0,0,,And this causes a rupture in your identity,\N{\rChinese}这导致你的身份出现断裂，
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.90,0:08:50.52,English,,0,0,0,,in your coherent sense of the world, which destroys your worldview.\N{\rChinese}在你连贯的世界观中，摧毁了你的世界观。
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.72,0:08:52.70,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? And this leads to depression.\N{\rChinese}好的？这就导致了抑郁。
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.30,0:08:54.46,English,,0,0,0,,What is depression?\N{\rChinese}抑郁是什么？
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.88,0:09:00.38,English,,0,0,0,,Depression is the inability to act\N{\rChinese}抑郁就是行动不遂。
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.38,0:09:04.60,English,,0,0,0,,and to think. Okay? You don't know what you want to accomplish.\N{\rChinese}然后去思考。好吧？你不知道自己想完成什么。
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.00,0:09:06.82,English,,0,0,0,,You don't trust yourself.\N{\rChinese}你不相信自己。
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.16,0:09:08.52,English,,0,0,0,,You don't know what you like.\N{\rChinese}你不知道自己喜欢什么。
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.80,0:09:10.40,English,,0,0,0,,And so what are the symptoms of depression?\N{\rChinese}[163] 那么抑郁的症状是什么？
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.74,0:09:14.18,English,,0,0,0,,You sleep a lot. You find no pleasure in anything.\N{\rChinese}[164] 你睡得很多，什么事都找不到乐趣。
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.36,0:09:17.96,English,,0,0,0,,You feel no emotion.\N{\rChinese}[165] 你没有任何情绪。
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.22,0:09:20.46,English,,0,0,0,,You feel sort of numbness. Okay? And that's why people,\N{\rChinese}你有点麻木的感觉。好吧？这就是人们的原因。
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.62,0:09:25.66,English,,0,0,0,,they tend to take drugs or they just sleep all the time or whatever.\N{\rChinese}他们往往会服药，或者整天睡觉，或者随便而已。
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.32,0:09:27.82,English,,0,0,0,,All right? Because you're unable to act.\N{\rChinese}好吧？因为你没能行动。
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.92,0:09:32.60,English,,0,0,0,,And that's exactly what's happening to Odysseus, Penelope, and Tanaka.\N{\rChinese}这正是奥德修斯、佩妮洛普和田中所经历的。
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.30,0:09:35.78,English,,0,0,0,,All right? There's a trauma in their lives.\N{\rChinese}好吧？他们的生活中有一次创伤。
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.12,0:09:38.20,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? And they just believe this as well.\N{\rChinese}好吧？他们也这么相信。
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.32,0:09:41.86,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? There could be a trauma that splits the soul.\N{\rChinese}好的？可能有一次创伤把灵魂撕开。
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.06,0:09:44.92,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? And it could be a demon.\N{\rChinese}好的？它也可能是个魔鬼。
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.18,0:09:48.90,English,,0,0,0,,It could be a really painful incident.\N{\rChinese}它可能是一件非常痛苦的事件。
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.90,0:09:51.24,English,,0,0,0,,It could be anything. Okay? But it splits your soul.\N{\rChinese}它可以是任何事。好吧？但它会撕裂你的灵魂。
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.38,0:09:56.34,English,,0,0,0,,And if you are to recover, then you have to repair your soul.\N{\rChinese}如果你要恢复，就得修复自己的灵魂。
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.66,0:09:59.36,English,,0,0,0,,And that's a fundamental conflict and\N{\rChinese}而这就是奥德赛中的基本冲突，以及其中的一个难题。
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.36,0:10:01.46,English,,0,0,0,,a dilemma within the Odyssey.\N{\rChinese}而这就是奥德赛中的基本冲突，以及其中的一个难题。
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.78,0:10:03.20,English,,0,0,0,,You have three individuals,\N{\rChinese}你有三个人，
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.00,0:10:06.00,English,,0,0,0,,Odysseus, Penelope, and Tanaka.\N{\rChinese}奥德修斯、佩内洛普和田中。
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.20,0:10:08.00,English,,0,0,0,,Their soul has been splintered.\N{\rChinese}他们的灵魂已碎裂。
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.06,0:10:11.06,English,,0,0,0,,And so they're on a journey, their own Odyssey,\N{\rChinese}于是他们踏上旅程，自己的奥德赛
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.30,0:10:13.98,English,,0,0,0,,to repair their soul.\N{\rChinese}修复他们的灵魂。
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.70,0:10:18.48,English,,0,0,0,,And the answer, of course, is each other.\N{\rChinese}答案当然是彼此。
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.48,0:10:20.26,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? Their love for each other.\N{\rChinese}好的？他们彼此的爱。
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.34,0:10:23.02,English,,0,0,0,,That's what's going to save the world.\N{\rChinese}那就是拯救世界的关键。
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.12,0:10:24.90,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? The love of family.\N{\rChinese}好的？家族之爱。
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.52,0:10:30.80,English,,0,0,0,,And that is the fundamental message of the Odyssey.\N{\rChinese}这就是《奥德赛》的根本信息。
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.60,0:10:35.14,English,,0,0,0,,All right? And that's why it's such a powerful read.\N{\rChinese}好的？这就是它如此精彩的原因。
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.26,0:10:37.52,English,,0,0,0,,Okay. So\N{\rChinese}好的。
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.52,0:10:41.66,English,,0,0,0,,let me give you some background as to the plot.\N{\rChinese}让我先给你们介绍一下情节背景。
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.96,0:10:47.38,English,,0,0,0,,So, as you know, the Odyssey begins in immediate rest.\N{\rChinese}所以，正如你们所知，《奥德赛》一开始就处于即刻的休止。
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.64,0:10:50.20,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? And it's a story about two middle things, which is to say that\N{\rChinese}好的？这是一段关于两件中间事物的故事，意思是……
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.20,0:10:52.10,English,,0,0,0,,a lot of things have already taken place and\N{\rChinese}许多事已发生
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.10,0:10:55.40,English,,0,0,0,,happens just in the middle of the plot.\N{\rChinese}发生在情节中段。
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.86,0:10:57.96,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? In the beginning,\N{\rChinese}好的吗？一开始，
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.36,0:11:00.78,English,,0,0,0,,Odysseus has been away for 20 years.\N{\rChinese}奥德修斯已离开二十年。
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.34,0:11:03.08,English,,0,0,0,,And he's stuck on an island with Calypso.\N{\rChinese}他与卡吕普索一起被困在一座岛上。
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.12,0:11:07.44,English,,0,0,0,,Penelope is depressed and sitting by herself in the room.\N{\rChinese}佩妮洛普郁郁地坐在房间里。
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.62,0:11:08.92,English,,0,0,0,,Tanaka is angry. Okay?\N{\rChinese}田中愤怒。好的吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.00,0:11:12.20,English,,0,0,0,,And Athena comes and tells Tanaka, come with me.\N{\rChinese}雅典娜出现，告诉田中，跟我来。
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.28,0:11:13.70,English,,0,0,0,,I will help you find your father.\N{\rChinese}我会帮你找到父亲。
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.86,0:11:16.88,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So,\N{\rChinese}好的吗？所以，
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.00,0:11:22.26,English,,0,0,0,,Okay. So, the story starts with the Trojan War, of course.\N{\rChinese}好的。于是，故事就从特洛伊战争开始，当然。
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.44,0:11:27.06,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So remember, Helen has been taken to Troy.\N{\rChinese}好的吗？记住，海伦已被带到特洛伊。
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.14,0:11:29.58,English,,0,0,0,,She falls in love with Paris because\N{\rChinese}她爱上帕里斯，因为……
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.58,0:11:32.92,English,,0,0,0,,that's what Aphrodite promised Paris as a prize.\N{\rChinese}那是阿佛洛狄给帕里斯的奖赏。
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.68,0:11:37.60,English,,0,0,0,,And now her husband, the king of Sparta,\N{\rChinese}现在她的丈夫，斯巴达国王，
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.80,0:11:41.30,English,,0,0,0,,Menelaus, and his brother,\N{\rChinese}梅内劳斯，和他的兄弟，
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.48,0:11:45.96,English,,0,0,0,,Agamemnon, the king of kings, are like, we're going to raise an army and we're going to get back Helen.\N{\rChinese}阿伽墨农，王中之王，我们要组军去取回海伦。
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.08,0:11:48.26,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? And this is prophesized.\N{\rChinese}好的？这就是预言的内容。
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.92,0:11:52.66,English,,0,0,0,,This is to be the greatest war in human history.\N{\rChinese}这将成为人类历史上最伟大的战争。
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.84,0:11:56.66,English,,0,0,0,,It will make mortals into gods.\N{\rChinese}它会让凡人变成神。
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.90,0:12:00.12,English,,0,0,0,,Right? That's why Achilles enters this war.\N{\rChinese}对吧？这就是阿基琉斯投身此战的原因。
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.32,0:12:03.26,English,,0,0,0,,Because this is the opportunity for him to prove that\N{\rChinese}因为这是他证明自己的机会。
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.26,0:12:06.68,English,,0,0,0,,he is the greatest warrior in all of human history.\N{\rChinese}他要证明自己是人类历史上最伟大的战士。
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.92,0:12:08.32,English,,0,0,0,,And that's why he goes to Troy.\N{\rChinese}于是他就去投身特洛伊。
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.04,0:12:14.52,English,,0,0,0,,Odysseus is also supposed to go to this war.\N{\rChinese}奥德修斯也应该去这场战争。
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.68,0:12:16.24,English,,0,0,0,,But Odysseus, he's not.\N{\rChinese}但奥德修斯却没有去。
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.24,0:12:19.46,English,,0,0,0,,He's different from Achilles. Because\N{\rChinese}他与阿基琉斯不同。因为
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.46,0:12:21.66,English,,0,0,0,,Odysseus loves his wife, Penelope.\N{\rChinese}奥德修斯爱他的妻子佩妮洛普。
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.86,0:12:26.94,English,,0,0,0,,And he has a new son, six months old, Tanakes.\N{\rChinese}而且他有个新儿子，六个月大的塔纳克斯。
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.20,0:12:28.64,English,,0,0,0,,So he's conflicted.\N{\rChinese}于是他心里有点纠结。
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.84,0:12:30.44,English,,0,0,0,,And he really doesn't want to go to war.\N{\rChinese}而且他真的是不想去打仗。
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.78,0:12:34.26,English,,0,0,0,,But the Greeks need him because the gods have told the Greeks\N{\rChinese}但希腊人需要他，因为众神已告诉他们。
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.26,0:12:36.92,English,,0,0,0,,that it is really Odysseus who will win the war.\N{\rChinese}那是奥德修斯真正赢得战争的人。
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.08,0:12:40.76,English,,0,0,0,,Because he's the one who will come up with the Trojan horse, the stratagem that will win this war.\N{\rChinese}因为他是那个会想出木马计策的，能赢得这场战争的人。
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.94,0:12:42.56,English,,0,0,0,,So you need this guy. Okay?\N{\rChinese}所以你需要这个人。
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.82,0:12:44.08,English,,0,0,0,,So Odysseus doesn't want to go.\N{\rChinese}于是奥德修斯不想去。
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.36,0:12:45.72,English,,0,0,0,,But the Greeks insist.\N{\rChinese}但希腊人坚持。
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.72,0:12:49.66,English,,0,0,0,,So the Greeks send two messengers to Ithaca\N{\rChinese}于是希腊人派两名使者去伊塔卡。
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.66,0:12:52.60,English,,0,0,0,,where Odysseus lives.\N{\rChinese}在奥德修斯居住的地方。
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.04,0:12:58.06,English,,0,0,0,,Now Odysseus, what he does is he pretends to be mad.\N{\rChinese}于是奥德修斯，所做的事是装疯。
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.40,0:12:59.84,English,,0,0,0,,So he dresses up like a beggar.\N{\rChinese}于是他打扮成乞人。
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.90,0:13:02.82,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? He's a king. But he dresses up really badly.\N{\rChinese}好的？他是国王，但他打扮得很糟。
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.00,0:13:07.62,English,,0,0,0,,And he's going around the farmland and throwing salt everywhere he goes.\N{\rChinese}他在田间走来走去，撒盐到处处。
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.76,0:13:11.68,English,,0,0,0,,He looks crazy. Okay? And you throw salt in the land to kill crops.\N{\rChinese}他看起来很疯，撒盐到田里去杀庄稼。
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.18,0:13:14.84,English,,0,0,0,,So he looks kind of crazy. But the Greeks...\N{\rChinese}于是他看起来有点疯。可是希腊人……
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.84,0:13:18.72,English,,0,0,0,,But the Greeks understand that this is a man of disguise.\N{\rChinese}但希腊人知道这是一位伪装高手。
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.30,0:13:21.86,English,,0,0,0,,He's a man of stratagems.\N{\rChinese}他是个诡计高手。
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.16,0:13:24.58,English,,0,0,0,,He's very clever. So it's probably a trick.\N{\rChinese}他很聪明，应该是个诡计。
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.92,0:13:28.44,English,,0,0,0,,So what they do is they take his six -month -old son,\N{\rChinese}于是他们把他六个月大的儿子，塔马库斯，取出来，
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.84,0:13:30.16,English,,0,0,0,,Tammacus. Okay?\N{\rChinese}好吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.26,0:13:33.32,English,,0,0,0,,And put him in front of Odysseus.\N{\rChinese}把他放在奥德修斯面前。
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.42,0:13:36.50,English,,0,0,0,,Now Odysseus is plowing the field and salting the fields.\N{\rChinese}现在奥德修斯正耕田撒盐。
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.58,0:13:38.38,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? And basically the test is this.\N{\rChinese}好吧？基本上考验就是这样。
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.48,0:13:42.32,English,,0,0,0,,If you're really mad, you're going to run over your son, Tammacus, and kill him.\N{\rChinese}如果你真是疯了，就会跑去把你的儿子塔马库斯杀掉。
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.56,0:13:44.18,English,,0,0,0,,If you're not mad...\N{\rChinese}如果你没疯……
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.18,0:13:47.24,English,,0,0,0,,If you're not really crazy, then you're going to stop\N{\rChinese}如果你真没疯，那就会停下来。
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.24,0:13:49.10,English,,0,0,0,,and go somewhere else and save your son.\N{\rChinese}去别处去，救你的儿子。
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.36,0:13:51.24,English,,0,0,0,,So let's see if you're really crazy.\N{\rChinese}好了，看看你到底有多疯。
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.12,0:13:56.24,English,,0,0,0,,And so Odysseus, of course, turns away\N{\rChinese}于是，奥德修斯当然转身离去。
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.24,0:13:58.32,English,,0,0,0,,and saves his son. And the Greeks are like, Ha!\N{\rChinese}并救了他的儿子。希腊人们则笑道，哈！
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.46,0:14:00.06,English,,0,0,0,,You see? You're tricking us all along.\N{\rChinese}你看到了吧？你一直在把我们骗过去。
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.14,0:14:02.94,English,,0,0,0,,Come with us to Troy.\N{\rChinese}跟我们一起去特洛伊吧。
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.10,0:14:05.44,English,,0,0,0,,And so Odysseus has no choice but to go.\N{\rChinese}于是，奥德修斯无路可走，只能出发。
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.98,0:14:09.84,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So this is why Odysseus goes.\N{\rChinese}好吧？这就是奥德修斯出发的原因。
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.98,0:14:12.16,English,,0,0,0,,He's forced to go. But you think about it.\N{\rChinese}他被迫离去。你想想看。
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.22,0:14:13.66,English,,0,0,0,,This story doesn't really make any sense.\N{\rChinese}这个故事真的没什么意义。
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.40,0:14:17.58,English,,0,0,0,,Right? And that's the greatness of Homer.\N{\rChinese}对吧？这就是荷马的伟大之处。
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.84,0:14:21.36,English,,0,0,0,,Because he's telling us the complexity of human psychology.\N{\rChinese}因为他在告诉我们人类心理的复杂性。
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.46,0:14:23.86,English,,0,0,0,,Odysseus is really, really smart.\N{\rChinese}奥德修斯真是非常聪明。
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.06,0:14:26.68,English,,0,0,0,,He thinks ahead. Right? He should know that\N{\rChinese}他会提前思考。对吧？他应该知道，
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.68,0:14:31.34,English,,0,0,0,,if he were to have this strategy, the Greeks would see through it really quickly.\N{\rChinese}如果他采用这种策略，希腊人很快就会看穿。
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.54,0:14:34.90,English,,0,0,0,,Right? So what he should be doing is hiding from the Greeks.\N{\rChinese}对吧？他应该做的就是躲避希腊人。
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.02,0:14:39.32,English,,0,0,0,,Right? Or maybe just moving away.\N{\rChinese}对吧？或者只是搬离。
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.76,0:14:42.70,English,,0,0,0,,If you really, really don't want to go to this war, you just run away.\N{\rChinese}如果你真的不想去这场战争，就跑掉吧。
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.70,0:14:43.96,English,,0,0,0,,And take your family with you.\N{\rChinese}把家人一起带走。
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.38,0:14:45.84,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? Or you know what?\N{\rChinese}好吧？或者你知道怎么做？
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.16,0:14:48.30,English,,0,0,0,,Just kill these guys. Because you're crazy.\N{\rChinese}直接把这几个人干掉。因为你很疯狂。
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.42,0:14:50.72,English,,0,0,0,,Right? All right?\N{\rChinese}对吧？全部都好？
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.76,0:14:54.18,English,,0,0,0,,So what this tells us is\N{\rChinese}所以这告诉我们的就是
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.18,0:14:58.70,English,,0,0,0,,that, yes, Odysseus really loves his family.\N{\rChinese}是的，奥德修斯真的很爱他的家人。
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.86,0:15:02.06,English,,0,0,0,,And he wants to be with his family.\N{\rChinese}他想和家人一起。
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.22,0:15:04.74,English,,0,0,0,,Because he knows that if he goes to Troy, he'll be gone for 20 years.\N{\rChinese}因为他知道去特洛伊会离家二十年。
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.46,0:15:10.20,English,,0,0,0,,That's 20 years that he won't be able to see his son, Tammacus, grow up.\N{\rChinese}二十年里他看不到儿子塔马库斯成长。
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.56,0:15:12.86,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? But at the same time,\N{\rChinese}好的？但与此同时，
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.98,0:15:15.54,English,,0,0,0,,this is the greatest war in human history.\N{\rChinese}这是人类历史上最大的战争。
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.04,0:15:17.88,English,,0,0,0,,Achilles is going. Achaemenon is going.\N{\rChinese}阿基琉斯要去，阿赫美尼翁也要去。
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.54,0:15:20.62,English,,0,0,0,,Does Odysseus really want to be left out?\N{\rChinese}奥德修斯真的想被留下吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.14,0:15:26.06,English,,0,0,0,,Does he really want to be the one guy who's like a coward?\N{\rChinese}他真的想成为那个唯一的胆小子吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.26,0:15:28.08,English,,0,0,0,,Who's like, you know what? I'm just going to stay home.\N{\rChinese}谁说的，嗯，我就回家去。
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.04,0:15:33.66,English,,0,0,0,,Right? The Greeks will just laugh at him for the rest of his life saying, you're just a pussy.\N{\rChinese}对吧？希腊人会一直嘲笑他，叫他是只小毛虫。
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.60,0:15:37.38,English,,0,0,0,,Right? You've been pussy whipped by your wife.\N{\rChinese}对吧？你被老婆打得像只小毛虫。
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.58,0:15:39.48,English,,0,0,0,,He doesn't want to do that. So it's a conflict.\N{\rChinese}他不想这么做。于是就产生了冲突。
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.84,0:15:43.06,English,,0,0,0,,Right? So what he does is he comes up with a stratagem that\N{\rChinese}对吧？于是他想出了一个计策
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.06,0:15:46.48,English,,0,0,0,,allows the Greeks to see through it really quickly\N{\rChinese}让希腊人很快看透它
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.48,0:15:51.10,English,,0,0,0,,and force him to go so he doesn't have to bear any responsibility for what he does.\N{\rChinese}并逼他去做事，这样他就不用为所作承担责任
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.88,0:15:55.36,English,,0,0,0,,All right? And that is a complexity of the human soul.\N{\rChinese}对吧？这就是人心的复杂性。
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.46,0:15:57.72,English,,0,0,0,,That is a complexity of our worldview.\N{\rChinese}这就是我们世界观的复杂性。
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.96,0:16:02.48,English,,0,0,0,,All right? So he goes to Troy\N{\rChinese}对吧？于是他去特洛伊
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.48,0:16:07.74,English,,0,0,0,,and he has to explain to himself why he's there.\N{\rChinese}然后他得自己解释为什么在那里
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.74,0:16:10.82,English,,0,0,0,,And he knows he's going to be away from home for 20 years,\N{\rChinese}他知道自己将离家20年，
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.88,0:16:13.04,English,,0,0,0,,10 years in Troy, 10 years being lost at sea.\N{\rChinese}10年在特洛伊，10年在海上漂泊
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.32,0:16:15.44,English,,0,0,0,,Right? So his worldview is this.\N{\rChinese}对吧？于是他的世界观就是这样。
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.08,0:16:21.44,English,,0,0,0,,Why am I here in Troy?\N{\rChinese}我为什么会在特洛伊呢？
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.78,0:16:26.20,English,,0,0,0,,Well, the first reason is just justice.\N{\rChinese}好吧，第一理由就是正义。
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.94,0:16:31.20,English,,0,0,0,,Right? This is a just war because\N{\rChinese}对吧？这是一场正义之战。
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.20,0:16:34.70,English,,0,0,0,,the Trojans stole Helen.\N{\rChinese}特洛伊人抢走了海伦。
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.70,0:16:36.02,English,,0,0,0,,And therefore\N{\rChinese}于是
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.02,0:16:41.92,English,,0,0,0,,the Greeks must avenge the honor of Menelaus.\N{\rChinese}希腊必须为墨涅劳斯的荣誉报仇。
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.38,0:16:45.00,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? Second is family.\N{\rChinese}好吧？第二个是家族。
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.14,0:16:49.24,English,,0,0,0,,Helen should be with her children.\N{\rChinese}海伦应该和她的孩子们在一起。
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.62,0:16:53.48,English,,0,0,0,,Helen should be with her family in Sparta.\N{\rChinese}海伦应该和她的家族在斯巴达。
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.94,0:16:57.36,English,,0,0,0,,We have to return her to Sparta.\N{\rChinese}我们要把她送回斯巴达。
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.86,0:17:00.26,English,,0,0,0,,How would I feel if Penelope were stolen from me?\N{\rChinese}如果佩内洛普被抢走，我会怎样感受？
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.36,0:17:03.60,English,,0,0,0,,I would want everyone to go fight with me to get her back as well.\N{\rChinese}我想让大家一起去战斗，拿回她。
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.70,0:17:05.96,English,,0,0,0,,Right? So I'm going to go fight with my family. Okay?\N{\rChinese}对吧？所以我要和家族一起去战斗。好吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.10,0:17:09.24,English,,0,0,0,,Now, third reason is legacy.\N{\rChinese}现在，第三个理由是遗产。
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.62,0:17:15.36,English,,0,0,0,,Yes, he will not see his son,\N{\rChinese}是的，他会在二十年里看不到他的儿子，
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.42,0:17:16.80,English,,0,0,0,,Timarchus, for 20 years.\N{\rChinese}提马尔库斯，
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.44,0:17:20.52,English,,0,0,0,,Therefore, he has to build him a legacy\N{\rChinese}因此，他必须为他建造一段遗产。
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.52,0:17:24.40,English,,0,0,0,,that will carry him for the rest of his life.\N{\rChinese}那将伴随他余生。
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.60,0:17:28.12,English,,0,0,0,,If he is in Troy and he wins this great war\N{\rChinese}若他在特洛伊并赢得这场大战
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.12,0:17:31.08,English,,0,0,0,,and becomes this great hero, then\N{\rChinese}并成为伟大英雄，
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.08,0:17:34.68,English,,0,0,0,,Timarchus himself will be famous as a son of a Trojan.\N{\rChinese}提马尔库斯本人将因是特洛伊之子而闻名。
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.68,0:17:38.36,English,,0,0,0,,He will be the son of Odysseus. People will respect Timarchus.\N{\rChinese}他将是奥德修斯之子。人们会敬佩提马尔库斯。
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.58,0:17:40.48,English,,0,0,0,,He wants to build a legacy for his son.\N{\rChinese}他想为自己的儿子打造一段遗产。
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.58,0:17:42.68,English,,0,0,0,,He wants to tell his son,\N{\rChinese}他想对儿子说，
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.84,0:17:45.52,English,,0,0,0,,this is how you should live your life.\N{\rChinese}这就是你应该过的生活。
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.68,0:17:49.40,English,,0,0,0,,You should live a life of honor, of justice, of truth.\N{\rChinese}你要过一种荣耀、正义、真理的生活。
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.82,0:17:55.50,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So these are the three reasons why he goes to Troy.\N{\rChinese}好的？所以这就是他去特洛伊的三个理由。
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.00,0:18:01.30,English,,0,0,0,,And we have to remember that this is all to justify his conflict.\N{\rChinese}我们要记住，这一切都是为了证明他的冲突。
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.44,0:18:03.30,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? There's a conflict. There's a rupture in his soul.\N{\rChinese}好的？有冲突，心里也有裂痕。
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.42,0:18:08.62,English,,0,0,0,,He needs to mend it by explaining why he's doing what he's doing.\N{\rChinese}他需要通过解释自己所做之事来修补它。
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.56,0:18:12.38,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? Because again, he's abandoned his family for 20 years.\N{\rChinese}好吧？因为他又一次，离开了家人二十年。
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.12,0:18:14.74,English,,0,0,0,,Okay. So\N{\rChinese}好的。
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.74,0:18:19.06,English,,0,0,0,,what's going to happen is this.\N{\rChinese}接下来会发生的事就是这样。
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.22,0:18:23.72,English,,0,0,0,,This is the worldview that Odysseus has when he enters Troy.\N{\rChinese}这是奥德修斯进入特洛伊时的世界观。
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.74,0:18:28.78,English,,0,0,0,,The problem starts when they win the war.\N{\rChinese}问题在于他们赢得战争之后。
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.10,0:18:32.22,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? Because when they win the war, then Odysseus, he's going to be the king of the world.\N{\rChinese}好的？因为他们赢得战争后，奥德修斯就会成为世界之王。
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.22,0:18:35.06,English,,0,0,0,,And Odysseus is forced to see that\N{\rChinese}而奥德修斯被迫看到
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.06,0:18:40.48,English,,0,0,0,,all of these three things were wrong.\N{\rChinese}这三件事都错了。
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.10,0:18:44.46,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? He will discover that\N{\rChinese}好的？他会发现
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.46,0:18:46.06,English,,0,0,0,,this war was not about justice.\N{\rChinese}这场战争不是关于正义的。
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.44,0:18:49.12,English,,0,0,0,,It was just about revenge and murder.\N{\rChinese}只是关于复仇与杀戮。
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.62,0:18:51.28,English,,0,0,0,,It is about family.\N{\rChinese}它关乎家庭。
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.34,0:18:54.12,English,,0,0,0,,It's about destroying families. Because when\N{\rChinese}它关乎破坏家庭。因为当
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.12,0:18:57.56,English,,0,0,0,,you win this war, you enslave the woman and kill the husbands.\N{\rChinese}你赢得这场战争，你奴役女人并杀死丈夫。
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.08,0:18:59.86,English,,0,0,0,,Right? That's destroying families.\N{\rChinese}对吧？那就是破坏家庭。
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.64,0:19:02.44,English,,0,0,0,,And it's not about legacy. It's about legacy because\N{\rChinese}而且不是关于遗产。是关于遗产，因为
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.44,0:19:05.44,English,,0,0,0,,you've destroyed the Trojan civilization\N{\rChinese}你已经毁灭了特洛伊文明
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.44,0:19:08.84,English,,0,0,0,,for no particular reason.\N{\rChinese}无特定原因。
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.98,0:19:11.96,English,,0,0,0,,Because Helen doesn't even want to go back to Sparta.\N{\rChinese}因为海伦甚至不想回到斯巴达。
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.56,0:19:15.36,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? And this causes cognitive dissonance.\N{\rChinese}于是产生认知失调。
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.06,0:19:19.90,English,,0,0,0,,This is what causes\N{\rChinese}这就是原因
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.90,0:19:25.80,English,,0,0,0,,his PTSD or trauma.\N{\rChinese}他的创伤后应激或创伤
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.12,0:19:31.76,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So the Odyssey is his journey.\N{\rChinese}好的？所以《奥德赛》是他的旅程。
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.76,0:19:35.16,English,,0,0,0,,His journey to repair his soul so that he can go home.\N{\rChinese}他的旅程是修复灵魂，让他能归家。
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.78,0:19:37.04,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? Does it make sense, guys?\N{\rChinese}好吧？这样说通吗，大家？
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.42,0:19:39.64,English,,0,0,0,,That's what the Odyssey is about. Okay.\N{\rChinese}这就是《奥德赛》的主题。好。
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.06,0:19:46.00,English,,0,0,0,,So what we're going to do now is we are going to read certain sections.\N{\rChinese}所以我们现在要做的事是读一些特定章节。
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.16,0:19:47.84,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So this is from the Iliad actually.\N{\rChinese}好吧？这其实是来自《伊利亚特》。
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.36,0:19:49.58,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? This is from the Iliad.\N{\rChinese}好吧？这来自《伊利亚特》。
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.92,0:19:54.84,English,,0,0,0,,And so remember in book one of the Iliad,\N{\rChinese}记住《伊利亚特》第一卷的情节，
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.90,0:19:59.08,English,,0,0,0,,Achilles and Agamemnon have this nasty fight where Achilles is like, screw you, you're a dog.\N{\rChinese}阿基琉斯和阿伽门农发生了一场激烈的争斗，阿基琉斯说：我去你吧，你这只狗。
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.18,0:20:00.42,English,,0,0,0,,I'm not going to fight for you ever again.\N{\rChinese}我再也不为你而战了。
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.82,0:20:02.58,English,,0,0,0,,Agamemnon is like, screw you, you're a dog. Screw you, I don't need you.\N{\rChinese}阿伽门农说：我去你吧，你这只狗，我不需要你。
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.76,0:20:05.78,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? But in book two, Agamemnon recognizes that, oh,\N{\rChinese}好吧？但在第二卷，阿伽门农意识到，哦，这实际上是个问题，因为阿基琉斯是我们最伟大的战士。
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.96,0:20:09.74,English,,0,0,0,,this is actually a problem because Achilles is the greatest warrior that we have.\N{\rChinese}好吧？但在第二卷，阿伽门农意识到，哦，这实际上是个问题，因为阿基琉斯是我们最伟大的战士。
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.96,0:20:13.62,English,,0,0,0,,And if Achilles doesn't want to fight, then that's bad for morale.\N{\rChinese}如果阿基琉斯不想战斗，那就会影响士气。
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.38,0:20:15.94,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? We might actually lose this war.\N{\rChinese}好吧？我们可能真的会输这场战争。
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.46,0:20:18.36,English,,0,0,0,,So Agamemnon being stupid,\N{\rChinese}于是阿伽门农也很傻，
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.72,0:20:20.50,English,,0,0,0,,he has this stupid idea.\N{\rChinese}他也有这个傻想法。
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.62,0:20:24.88,English,,0,0,0,,And this stupid idea is this. How can I rally my soldiers?\N{\rChinese}而这个傻想法就是这样。我要怎么召集我的士兵？
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.26,0:20:28.38,English,,0,0,0,,How can I galvanize them into action now\N{\rChinese}我要怎么把他们调动起来做行动？
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.38,0:20:30.58,English,,0,0,0,,that Achilles has abandoned battlefield?\N{\rChinese}那是阿基琉斯已离开战场？
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.96,0:20:35.30,English,,0,0,0,,I don't know. I'll tell them they can go home.\N{\rChinese}我不晓得。我会告诉他们可以回家。
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.56,0:20:37.64,English,,0,0,0,,Ha. Reverse psychology, guys.\N{\rChinese}哈。逆向心理，伙计们。
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.84,0:20:41.24,English,,0,0,0,,Right? Reverse psychology. Because when I say you guys can go home,\N{\rChinese}对吧？逆向心理。因为我说你们可以回家，每个希腊人都会说：不。我们一路来到特洛，想为你赢得荣耀，…】
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.56,0:20:44.40,English,,0,0,0,,every Greek will be like, no.\N{\rChinese}】
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.40,0:20:49.78,English,,0,0,0,,We came all the way to Troy to win glory for you,\N{\rChinese}】
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.84,0:20:53.42,English,,0,0,0,,Agamemnon. We're going to fight to the death to ensure\N{\rChinese}阿加美农。我们要打到死去，确保你们获得荣耀，阿加美农。
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.42,0:20:54.86,English,,0,0,0,,that you get your glory, Agamemnon.\N{\rChinese}我们不想回家。别让我们回家。
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.02,0:20:57.26,English,,0,0,0,,We don't want to go home. Don't make us go home.\N{\rChinese}We don't want to go home. Don't make us go home.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.56,0:20:59.48,English,,0,0,0,,We're going to fight. Okay? So that's the plan.\N{\rChinese}我们要去打仗。好吧？这就是计划。
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.08,0:21:01.74,English,,0,0,0,,And of course, it doesn't matter.\N{\rChinese}当然，没什么大不了的。
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.74,0:21:04.58,English,,0,0,0,,It backfires. And when people hear,\N{\rChinese}反而起作用。人们听到后……
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.72,0:21:07.70,English,,0,0,0,,oh, we go home, they all run away.\N{\rChinese}哦，我们回家，他们都跑了。
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.98,0:21:10.40,English,,0,0,0,,And Agamemnon's like, he now has cognitive dissonance.\N{\rChinese}阿加美农说，他现在有认知失调。
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.48,0:21:11.96,English,,0,0,0,,He's like, what?\N{\rChinese}他问，怎么了？
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.36,0:21:14.88,English,,0,0,0,,Oh, what? He doesn't understand what's going on.\N{\rChinese}哦，怎么了？他不明白发生了什么事。
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.98,0:21:17.68,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? And at this point in the story,\N{\rChinese}好吧？在故事的这一点，
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.90,0:21:21.64,English,,0,0,0,,the war should be over because all the Greeks just went home.\N{\rChinese}战争本该结束，因为所有希腊人都回家了。
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.26,0:21:26.40,English,,0,0,0,,And again, what happens is Odysseus will come\N{\rChinese}又一次，发生的事是奥德修斯会出现
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.40,0:21:29.68,English,,0,0,0,,and save everyone because he will recognize\N{\rChinese}并拯救大家，因为他会认出
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.18,0:21:31.58,English,,0,0,0,,that Agamemnon's just being stupid.\N{\rChinese}阿加美农只是愚笨
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.58,0:21:36.86,English,,0,0,0,,And he will force all the Greeks to return back to their post.\N{\rChinese}他将迫使所有希腊人返回各自阵地。
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.98,0:21:39.10,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? All right. So, Ivory, can you read please?\N{\rChinese}好的？没问题。好了，象牙，请读一遍好吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.60,0:21:42.52,English,,0,0,0,,Testing his men. Testing his men, but\N{\rChinese}检验他的部下。检验他的部下，
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.52,0:21:44.94,English,,0,0,0,,he only made the spirit race inside their chests.\N{\rChinese}他只让灵魂在胸中奔跑。
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.14,0:21:47.72,English,,0,0,0,,All the rank and file who'd never heard his plan.\N{\rChinese}所有从军士都未曾听闻他的计策。
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.12,0:21:51.88,English,,0,0,0,,And the whole assembly surged like big waves at sea.\N{\rChinese}整个集结如大海浪般汹涌。
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.06,0:21:55.22,English,,0,0,0,,The Icarian sea when east and south winds drive it on,\N{\rChinese}当伊卡里海被东南风推送时，
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.34,0:21:58.38,English,,0,0,0,,blasting down in force from the clouds of Father Zeus.\N{\rChinese}从宙斯之云中猛烈冲击而下，
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.74,0:22:04.00,English,,0,0,0,,Or when the west wind shakes the deep -standing grain with hurricane gusts\N{\rChinese}或当西风摇晃深海之粒，带来飓风般的劲风。
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.00,0:22:05.46,English,,0,0,0,,that flatten down the stalks.\N{\rChinese}把它们压平在杆子上。
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.96,0:22:08.86,English,,0,0,0,,So the mass assembly of troops was shaken now.\N{\rChinese}于是大批部队被震动。
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.18,0:22:12.42,English,,0,0,0,,They cried an alarm and charged towards the ships and\N{\rChinese}他们大声呼喊，冲向船只。
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.42,0:22:16.72,English,,0,0,0,,the dust went whirling up from under rushing feet as the men jostled back\N{\rChinese}尘土随奔腾脚步旋起，众人相互推挤
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.72,0:22:18.12,English,,0,0,0,,and forth, shouting orders.\N{\rChinese}并往复，喊令。
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.94,0:22:23.72,English,,0,0,0,,Grapple the ships, drag them down to the bright sea, clean out the launching channels.\N{\rChinese}抓船，拖下光海，扫出发船道。
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.72,0:22:27.94,English,,0,0,0,,Shrill shouts hitting the heavens, fighters racing for home,\N{\rChinese}尖锐的喊声冲向天空，战士们奔向归途，
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.06,0:22:30.32,English,,0,0,0,,knocking the blacks out underneath the holes.\N{\rChinese}把黑色的洞口敲开，击落其下的黑物。
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.32,0:22:33.00,English,,0,0,0,,Okay, so this just shows you how stupid Agamemnon is.\N{\rChinese}好的，这就展示了阿伽马农有多笨拙。
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.14,0:22:35.78,English,,0,0,0,,Because Agamemnon thinks that his soldiers actually want to fight this war.\N{\rChinese}因为阿伽马农认为他的士兵们真的想打这场战争。
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.04,0:22:37.82,English,,0,0,0,,But all the soldiers are homesick.\N{\rChinese}但所有士兵都思乡。
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.82,0:22:39.10,English,,0,0,0,,They're sick of this stupid war.\N{\rChinese}他们厌倦这场愚蠢的战争。
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.46,0:22:42.10,English,,0,0,0,,They don't even know why they're in this war.\N{\rChinese}他们甚至不知道自己为何参加这场战争。
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.32,0:22:45.34,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So the moment that Agamemnon says, you guys can go home,\N{\rChinese}好的？于是阿伽马农说：你们可以回家了
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.44,0:22:48.04,English,,0,0,0,,they're all like, we're going to get home as soon as possible.\N{\rChinese}他们都说，尽快回家。
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.14,0:22:50.08,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? They miss their wives. They miss their children.\N{\rChinese}好吧？他们想念妻子。想念孩子。
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.52,0:22:53.42,English,,0,0,0,,All right? So Aphrodite\N{\rChinese}好吧？于是阿佛洛狄提
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.42,0:22:55.70,English,,0,0,0,,and Hera are up in the sky.\N{\rChinese}而赫尔在天空中。
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.86,0:22:59.90,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? Mount Olympus. And they watch this and like, oh my God.\N{\rChinese}好的？奥林匹斯山。然后他们看着，哦我的天。
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.92,0:23:02.32,English,,0,0,0,,They're like, oh my God. Agamemnon's going to lose us this war.\N{\rChinese}他们说，哦我的天。阿伽马农要让我们在这场战争中失利。
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.58,0:23:06.18,English,,0,0,0,,What a moron. And Hera says to Athena,\N{\rChinese}多么傻瓜。赫尔说给阿特娜，
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.64,0:23:09.14,English,,0,0,0,,oh sorry, sorry, sorry. It's not actually Hera and Aphrodite.\N{\rChinese}哦抱歉，抱歉，抱歉。其实不是赫尔和阿佛洛狄提。
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.14,0:23:13.04,English,,0,0,0,,It's Hera and Athena because they're the ones who lost the contest to Aphrodite.\N{\rChinese}是赫尔和阿特娜，因为他们是那位在与阿佛洛狄提的比赛中失利的人。
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.16,0:23:15.86,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? But Hera says to Athena, you get down there, man.\N{\rChinese}好的？但赫尔对阿特娜说，去那里吧，兄弟。
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.04,0:23:17.40,English,,0,0,0,,And you stop this.\N{\rChinese}我停下来了。
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.56,0:23:20.64,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So Athena rushes down and\N{\rChinese}好的？于是阿特娜冲下来。
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.64,0:23:22.56,English,,0,0,0,,he talks to Odysseus.\N{\rChinese}他跟奥德修斯说话。
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.82,0:23:29.66,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? All right. Can you read?\N{\rChinese}好吧？没问题。你能读吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.80,0:23:33.24,English,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry. And now they might have won their journey home.\N{\rChinese}我很抱歉。现在他们或许已赢得归途。
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.28,0:23:35.40,English,,0,0,0,,The men of Argos fighting the will of fate.\N{\rChinese}阿尔戈人之战，命运之意已战。
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.74,0:23:37.96,English,,0,0,0,,Yes. If Hera had not alerted Athena.\N{\rChinese}是的。若赫拉未召唤雅典娜。
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.44,0:23:42.66,English,,0,0,0,,Inconceivable. Child of Zeus whose battle shield is thunder.\N{\rChinese}不可思议。宙斯之子，战甲如雷。
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.10,0:23:45.38,English,,0,0,0,,Tireless one. Athena. What?\N{\rChinese}不息者。雅典娜。什么？
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.58,0:23:49.18,English,,0,0,0,,Is this the way? All the Argives flying home to their fatherland.\N{\rChinese}这就是路吗？所有阿尔戈人都飞回故乡。
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.44,0:23:51.18,English,,0,0,0,,Sailing over to seize Brodback.\N{\rChinese}航行至布罗德巴克。
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.60,0:23:55.48,English,,0,0,0,,Leaving Priam and all the men of Troy a trophy to glory over.\N{\rChinese}离开普里阿姆，留给特洛斯的众人一枚胜利之奖。
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.74,0:24:00.28,English,,0,0,0,,Helen Argos. Helen for whom so many Argives lost their lives in Troy.\N{\rChinese}海伦·阿尔戈。海伦，因她众多阿尔戈人赴特洛斯而失去生命。
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.28,0:24:01.86,English,,0,0,0,,Far from native land.\N{\rChinese}离故乡很远。
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.42,0:24:05.88,English,,0,0,0,,Go. Range the ranks of Achaeans armed in bronze.\N{\rChinese}去吧。排开装甲的阿卡伊人。
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.24,0:24:09.32,English,,0,0,0,,With your winning words hold back each man you find.\N{\rChinese}用你的胜利之词把每个人都收住。
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.72,0:24:12.24,English,,0,0,0,,Don't let them halt their rolling ships to sea.\N{\rChinese}不要让他们停下滚动的船去海上。
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.20,0:24:14.66,English,,0,0,0,,Okay. Can we read?\N{\rChinese}好的。我们可以读吗。
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.08,0:24:20.32,English,,0,0,0,,The bright -eyed goddess Pallas lost no time.\N{\rChinese}明眸女神帕拉斯毫不耽搁。
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.82,0:24:23.58,English,,0,0,0,,Down she flashed from the peaks of Mount Olympus.\N{\rChinese}她从奥林匹斯山峰闪现而下。
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.72,0:24:26.80,English,,0,0,0,,Quickly reached the ships and found Odysseus first.\N{\rChinese}迅速抵达船只，先见奥德修斯。
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.08,0:24:28.34,English,,0,0,0,,A mastermind like Zeus.\N{\rChinese}像宙斯的主谋者。
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.56,0:24:32.34,English,,0,0,0,,Still standing fast. He had not laid a hand in his back.\N{\rChinese}仍然稳立。手未落在背后。
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.68,0:24:36.58,English,,0,0,0,,Black benched hull. Such anguish racked from his heart and fighting spirit.\N{\rChinese}黑色船身。心中激起痛楚与战意。
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.16,0:24:40.46,English,,0,0,0,,Now close beside him the bright -eyed goddess stood and urged him on.\N{\rChinese}现在，明眸女神靠近他，站在他身旁，催促他前行。
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.04,0:24:42.24,English,,0,0,0,,Royal son of...\N{\rChinese}王子……
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.20,0:24:45.26,English,,0,0,0,,Laertes. Laertes. Odysseus.\N{\rChinese}拉埃特斯。拉埃特斯。奥德修斯。
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.30,0:24:47.62,English,,0,0,0,,Great testician. What?\N{\rChinese}伟大的试验者。什么？
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.72,0:24:51.00,English,,0,0,0,,Is this the way? Okay. So, um, so\N{\rChinese}这是方式吗？好吧。于是……
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.00,0:24:52.76,English,,0,0,0,,everyone's trying to go home and you would think that\N{\rChinese}大家都想回家，你会想……
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.76,0:24:57.22,English,,0,0,0,,Odysseus would be the first person to get on a ship to go back to see his son\N{\rChinese}奥德修斯会是第一个登船回去看他儿子和妻子的人。好吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.22,0:25:00.12,English,,0,0,0,,and his wife. Okay? So he's, um,\N{\rChinese}于是，他，呃，……
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.52,0:25:02.32,English,,0,0,0,,standing there. He's kind of confused.\N{\rChinese}他站在那里，略显困惑。
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.92,0:25:05.78,English,,0,0,0,,All right? So he's like, this doesn't make any sense to me.\N{\rChinese}好的？于是他说，这一切对我来说毫无意义。
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.84,0:25:08.86,English,,0,0,0,,Why would Agamemnon do this? But at the same time, he sort of shows you\N{\rChinese}为什么阿伽墨农会这么做？但同时，他也让你觉得……
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.86,0:25:10.84,English,,0,0,0,,that he actually doesn't really want to go home.\N{\rChinese}他实际上并不是真的想回家。
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.34,0:25:13.96,English,,0,0,0,,Right? Because if he really wanted to go home, he'd be home by now.\N{\rChinese}对吗？如果他真的想回家，到现在就已经回到家里了。
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.20,0:25:18.16,English,,0,0,0,,Keep on going. All you Argives flying home to your fatherland,\N{\rChinese}继续前进。你们这些阿尔基人正飞回祖国。
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.38,0:25:20.20,English,,0,0,0,,tumbling into your oarswept ships,\N{\rChinese}翻滚进你的桨划船，离开普里阿姆与所有特洛伊人，留下一枚奖杯供他们在荣耀中欢庆。
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.62,0:25:24.72,English,,0,0,0,,leaving Priam and all the men of Troy a trophy to glory over.\N{\rChinese}翻滚进你的桨划船，离开普里阿姆与所有特洛伊人，留下一枚奖杯供他们在荣耀中欢庆。
Dialogue: 0,0:25:27.18,0:25:29.50,English,,0,0,0,,Helen of Argos. Helen of Argos.\N{\rChinese}阿格斯的海伦。阿格斯的海伦。
Dialogue: 0,0:25:29.50,0:25:34.04,English,,0,0,0,,Helen of Argos. It was Helen for whom so many Argives lost their lives in Troy, far from native land.\N{\rChinese}阿格斯的海伦。正是这位海伦，让无数阿格斯人赴战，离乡去战。
Dialogue: 0,0:25:34.60,0:25:36.12,English,,0,0,0,,No, don't give up now.\N{\rChinese}不，别现在放弃。
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.48,0:25:38.96,English,,0,0,0,,Rang the Achaean ranks, with your winning words,\N{\rChinese}响起阿契亚军列，凭你的胜利之语。
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.06,0:25:42.74,English,,0,0,0,,hold back each man you find, don't let them haul the rolling ship to sea.\N{\rChinese}把你找到的每个人都挡住，别让他们把滚船拉上海去。
Dialogue: 0,0:25:43.70,0:25:45.08,English,,0,0,0,,He knew the goddess' voice.\N{\rChinese}他听见女神的声音。
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.54,0:25:49.28,English,,0,0,0,,He went on a run, flinging off his cape as Eurybates picked it up,\N{\rChinese}他奔跑，掷下披风，欧里巴特斯拾起
Dialogue: 0,0:25:49.44,0:25:53.18,English,,0,0,0,,the Herald of Ithaca always at his side,\N{\rChinese}伊塔卡的信使始终在侧
Dialogue: 0,0:25:53.32,0:25:56.68,English,,0,0,0,,coming face -to -face with Atreides' Agamemnon,\N{\rChinese}面对阿特里德斯的阿伽墨农，正面相遇。
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.88,0:25:59.72,English,,0,0,0,,he relieved him of his father's royal scepter.\N{\rChinese}他把父亲的王杖交给他。
Dialogue: 0,0:25:59.96,0:26:03.38,English,,0,0,0,,Its power can never die, and grasping it tightly off,\N{\rChinese}它的力量永不消亡，紧握着它。
Dialogue: 0,0:26:03.62,0:26:06.36,English,,0,0,0,,he strode the ships of Argives armed and bronze.\N{\rChinese}他踏上了阿尔吉夫的船只，船身装甲与青铜铠甲。
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.52,0:26:12.26,English,,0,0,0,,Okay, so he's now going to single handedly save the Greeks from losing this war,\N{\rChinese}好了，他现在要单枪救出希腊人，免得他们在这场战争中失利。
Dialogue: 0,0:26:12.38,0:26:15.80,English,,0,0,0,,okay? So, Athena,\N{\rChinese}好了？所以，雅典娜，
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.32,0:26:21.64,English,,0,0,0,,right? Athena is always part of Odysseus.\N{\rChinese}右吗？雅典娜总是奥德修斯的一部分。
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.70,0:26:23.12,English,,0,0,0,,It's part of his soul, right?\N{\rChinese}它是他灵魂的一部分，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.14,0:26:27.26,English,,0,0,0,,The intuition. And his intuition tells him, something's wrong here.\N{\rChinese}直觉。直觉告诉他，这里有点不对劲。
Dialogue: 0,0:26:27.44,0:26:31.52,English,,0,0,0,,I need to stop this, okay? Also, look at Agamemnon.\N{\rChinese}我得停下来，好吗？再看看阿伽墨农。
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.34,0:26:33.78,English,,0,0,0,,Agamemnon is frozen.\N{\rChinese}阿伽墨农已经停住了。
Dialogue: 0,0:26:34.16,0:26:38.82,English,,0,0,0,,He is so distraught, he's shut down, okay?\N{\rChinese}他很慌张，已经关机，好吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:26:39.02,0:26:40.42,English,,0,0,0,,His brain has stopped working.\N{\rChinese}他的脑子已经停止工作。
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.54,0:26:43.50,English,,0,0,0,,It's frozen, because this is not supposed to happen, right?\N{\rChinese}它已经冻结，因为这本来应该不会发生，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:26:43.72,0:26:46.60,English,,0,0,0,,When he says that you guys can go home, he wanted everyone to say,\N{\rChinese}当他说你们可以回家时，他想让大家都说，
Dialogue: 0,0:26:46.72,0:26:49.08,English,,0,0,0,,no, we're going to stay and fight for you, Agamemnon.\N{\rChinese}不，我们会留下来为你而战，阿伽墨农。
Dialogue: 0,0:26:49.58,0:26:51.40,English,,0,0,0,,All right, so it's kind of dissonance.\N{\rChinese}好的，算是有点不和谐。
Dialogue: 0,0:26:51.76,0:26:53.72,English,,0,0,0,,It's so much kind of dissonance that when\N{\rChinese}不止于此，正是如此不和谐。
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.72,0:26:56.82,English,,0,0,0,,Odysseus takes the royal scepter.\N{\rChinese}奥德修斯举起王杖。
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.90,0:27:01.54,English,,0,0,0,,Agamemnon, doesn't even notice. The royal scepter is part of his soul, right?\N{\rChinese}阿伽墨农根本不觉。王杖是他灵魂的一部分，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:27:01.68,0:27:04.16,English,,0,0,0,,It's his legacy. It's what gives him authority.\N{\rChinese}这是他的遗产，赋予他权威。
Dialogue: 0,0:27:04.42,0:27:08.48,English,,0,0,0,,He's the king of kings. And Odysseus just takes the crown from him\N{\rChinese}他是王中之王。奥德修斯刚把王冠夺走，说：不，我是现在的王，来拯救这场战争，好吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:27:08.48,0:27:12.68,English,,0,0,0,,and says, no, I'm the king for now to save this war, okay?\N{\rChinese}这句话正好展示奥德修斯为赢得这场战争的决心。
Dialogue: 0,0:27:13.04,0:27:17.60,English,,0,0,0,,And it just shows you how committed Odysseus is to winning this war.\N{\rChinese}And it just shows you how committed Odysseus is to winning this war.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.76,0:27:21.48,English,,0,0,0,,He really believes that this war is about justice,\N{\rChinese}他真相信这场战争是关于正义的
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.80,0:27:25.10,English,,0,0,0,,about family, about building a legacy for his son.\N{\rChinese}关于家族，关于为儿子建造遗产。
Dialogue: 0,0:27:25.20,0:27:27.52,English,,0,0,0,,So, he refuses to lose this war.\N{\rChinese}于是，他决意不输这场战争。
Dialogue: 0,0:27:28.34,0:27:29.64,English,,0,0,0,,All right, keep on going.\N{\rChinese}好的，继续吧。
Dialogue: 0,0:27:31.28,0:27:33.04,English,,0,0,0,,I thought I - Oh, sorry, sorry.\N{\rChinese}我想我——哦，抱歉，抱歉。
Dialogue: 0,0:27:33.28,0:27:35.32,English,,0,0,0,,Yeah. All right.\N{\rChinese}好的。
Dialogue: 0,0:27:35.90,0:27:40.82,English,,0,0,0,,All right. So, but\N{\rChinese}好的。于是，
Dialogue: 0,0:27:40.82,0:27:42.30,English,,0,0,0,,that's the Iliad, okay?\N{\rChinese}那就是《伊利亚特》了，行吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:27:42.40,0:27:46.22,English,,0,0,0,,And again, what will happen is that Odysseus will win this war,\N{\rChinese}再说一次，接下来会发生的是奥德修斯会赢得这场战争。
Dialogue: 0,0:27:46.28,0:27:50.62,English,,0,0,0,,and he will win eternal glory for himself with the stratagem of the Trojan horse, right?\N{\rChinese}他将凭借特洛伊木马的计谋赢得永恒的荣耀，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:27:51.14,0:27:54.78,English,,0,0,0,,Now, we go to the Odyssey.\N{\rChinese}现在，我们进入《奥德修斯》篇章。
Dialogue: 0,0:27:55.06,0:28:00.48,English,,0,0,0,,And in the Odyssey, we don't actually meet Odysseus for many,\N{\rChinese}在《奥德修斯》中，我们实际上要等到很多书才会遇到奥德修斯。
Dialogue: 0,0:28:00.58,0:28:01.78,English,,0,0,0,,many books, okay?\N{\rChinese}大约很多书之后，才会见到他。
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.86,0:28:05.68,English,,0,0,0,,It's only towards the middle that we meet Odysseus.\N{\rChinese}它只有在中间才会遇到奥德修斯。
Dialogue: 0,0:28:05.70,0:28:09.80,English,,0,0,0,,In the first few books, it's a story of Tammacus and his journey to find his father, okay?\N{\rChinese}前几本书是塔马库斯的故事，他去寻找父亲，行吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:28:10.32,0:28:12.62,English,,0,0,0,,And when we meet Odysseus,\N{\rChinese}当我们遇到奥德修斯时，
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.64,0:28:17.68,English,,0,0,0,,he's a very different person from the Iliad.\N{\rChinese}他在《伊利亚特》里是一个完全不同的人。
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.78,0:28:20.28,English,,0,0,0,,Remember, in the Iliad, he is trying to win this war.\N{\rChinese}记住，在《伊利亚特》中，他正试图赢得这场战争。
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.42,0:28:22.58,English,,0,0,0,,He's very energetic. He's galvanized.\N{\rChinese}他很有活力，充满了动力。
Dialogue: 0,0:28:22.78,0:28:24.56,English,,0,0,0,,He's very heroic, okay?\N{\rChinese}他很英勇，行吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:28:24.60,0:28:28.84,English,,0,0,0,,But when we see the Iliad, we see that he's a very heroic person. And when we see the Iliad, we see him in the Odyssey, he's a changed person.\N{\rChinese}但在《伊利亚特》中我们看到他很英勇；在《奥德赛》中我们看到他已变成另一人。
Dialogue: 0,0:28:29.10,0:28:30.72,English,,0,0,0,,In fact, he's a broken person.\N{\rChinese}事实上，他是一个破碎的人。
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.04,0:28:34.58,English,,0,0,0,,So, what's happening is that Odysseus\N{\rChinese}于是，发生的事是奥德修斯……
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.58,0:28:37.06,English,,0,0,0,,and his crew try to go home, and they get lost at sea.\N{\rChinese}他和船员们试着回家，却在海上迷失。
Dialogue: 0,0:28:37.16,0:28:40.22,English,,0,0,0,,They have many adventures, and they get shipwrecked on an island,\N{\rChinese}他们经历了许多冒险，最终在一座岛上船只沉没。
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.40,0:28:44.28,English,,0,0,0,,and he becomes the sex toy,\N{\rChinese}他变成了性玩具，
Dialogue: 0,0:28:44.54,0:28:48.24,English,,0,0,0,,okay, literally a sex toy, of a goddess named Calypso, all right?\N{\rChinese}好的，字面意思是性玩具，女神卡吕普索的玩具，没问题？
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.34,0:28:51.40,English,,0,0,0,,So, basically, he's getting raped every day at night,\N{\rChinese}于是，他基本上每天晚上都被强奸，
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.52,0:28:56.62,English,,0,0,0,,and then he goes to the beach and he cries. Okay?\N{\rChinese}然后他去海边，哭了。
Dialogue: 0,0:28:56.74,0:29:02.58,English,,0,0,0,,So, he's a prisoner of Calypso for many years,\N{\rChinese}于是，他在卡吕普索手中做了多年的囚徒，
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.68,0:29:04.74,English,,0,0,0,,and the gods, Zeus, Athena,\N{\rChinese}神们，宙斯、雅典娜，
Dialogue: 0,0:29:05.18,0:29:07.74,English,,0,0,0,,they get together and say, you know what?\N{\rChinese}他们聚在一起说，你知道吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:29:07.80,0:29:09.12,English,,0,0,0,,We can't have this happen anymore, okay?\N{\rChinese}我们不想再让它发生了，好吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.56,0:29:11.18,English,,0,0,0,,Odysseus needs to go home.\N{\rChinese}奥德修斯需要回家。
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.32,0:29:15.60,English,,0,0,0,,So, they send Hermes to tell Calypso, you have to send Odysseus home.\N{\rChinese}于是他们派赫尔墨斯去告诉卡吕普索，你得把奥德修斯送回家。
Dialogue: 0,0:29:15.70,0:29:18.68,English,,0,0,0,,The gods will it. And Calypso says, sure, why not?\N{\rChinese}神们决定了。卡吕普索说，当然，为什么不呢？
Dialogue: 0,0:29:18.82,0:29:23.42,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So, can you read? With that, the powerful giant killer sped away.\N{\rChinese}好了？那么你能读吗？于是那位强大的巨人杀手迅速离去。
Dialogue: 0,0:29:23.60,0:29:27.06,English,,0,0,0,,So, it's Hermes, okay? So, Hermes has told Calypso, you have to let this guy go.\N{\rChinese}于是，赫尔墨斯来了，好吗？于是赫尔墨斯告诉卡吕普索，你得让这家伙走。
Dialogue: 0,0:29:27.80,0:29:30.58,English,,0,0,0,,The queenly nymph sought out the great Odysseus,\N{\rChinese}女王般的仙女去寻找伟大的奥德修斯。
Dialogue: 0,0:29:30.66,0:29:33.84,English,,0,0,0,,the commands of Zeus still ringing in her ears, and\N{\rChinese}宙斯的命令仍在她耳边回响，且
Dialogue: 0,0:29:33.84,0:29:36.66,English,,0,0,0,,found him there on the headland, sitting, still,\N{\rChinese}他在半岛上被发现，坐着，静止，
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.84,0:29:38.98,English,,0,0,0,,weeping, his eyes never dry,\N{\rChinese}泪流不止，眼眶未干
Dialogue: 0,0:29:39.18,0:29:43.12,English,,0,0,0,,his sweet life flowing away with the tears he wept for his royal journey home,\N{\rChinese}他的甜蜜人生随泪水流去，回想他王者归途的旅程，
Dialogue: 0,0:29:43.32,0:29:45.18,English,,0,0,0,,since then no longer pleased.\N{\rChinese}自此以后已不再欢喜。
Dialogue: 0,0:29:45.50,0:29:50.08,English,,0,0,0,,So, he's sitting, he's still, he's weeping, his eyes never dry,\N{\rChinese}于是他坐着，仍在泪流，眼眶未干。
Dialogue: 0,0:29:50.62,0:29:53.82,English,,0,0,0,,and all he's thinking about is the past, okay?\N{\rChinese}和他想的全是过去，好吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:29:53.96,0:29:56.30,English,,0,0,0,,This is clear signs of, okay, this is clear signs of, okay, this is clear signs of, okay, this is clear signs of, depression,\N{\rChinese}这明显是……这明显是……这明显是……这明显是……抑郁的明显迹象，
Dialogue: 0,0:29:56.72,0:29:59.92,English,,0,0,0,,PDST, okay? Do you want to read?\N{\rChinese}PDST，好吗？你想读吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:30:00.66,0:30:05.44,English,,0,0,0,,In the night true he'd sleep with her in the arching cave.\N{\rChinese}在夜里，他会与她在弧形洞穴里睡觉。
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.66,0:30:10.18,English,,0,0,0,,He had no choice, unwilling lover alongside lover all too willing.\N{\rChinese}他没有选择，爱人与爱人同在，皆甘心。
Dialogue: 0,0:30:10.50,0:30:13.00,English,,0,0,0,,But all his days he sat on rocks and beaches,\N{\rChinese}但他所有日子都坐在岩石与海滩上。
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.24,0:30:16.16,English,,0,0,0,,wrenching his heart with sobs and groans in anguish,\N{\rChinese}用嗓声和咳嗓把心扯开，痛哭不止，
Dialogue: 0,0:30:16.46,0:30:19.34,English,,0,0,0,,gazing out over the barren sea through blinding tears.\N{\rChinese}眺望空旮海面，泪眼朦胧。
Dialogue: 0,0:30:19.58,0:30:20.94,English,,0,0,0,,Okay, so he's a broken man.\N{\rChinese}好了，他是个破碎的人。
Dialogue: 0,0:30:21.14,0:30:25.34,English,,0,0,0,,He's a very different person from the Iliad, okay?\N{\rChinese}他是《伊利亚特》里的人物完全不同，明白吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:30:25.42,0:30:27.04,English,,0,0,0,,So, now, the question then is why?\N{\rChinese}于是，现在的问题是为什么？
Dialogue: 0,0:30:27.36,0:30:30.30,English,,0,0,0,,What happened to him? All right?\N{\rChinese}他发生了什么事？好了么？
Dialogue: 0,0:30:30.76,0:30:33.64,English,,0,0,0,,So, Calypso says to Odysseus, you know what?\N{\rChinese}于是，卡吕普索对奥德修斯说：你知道吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:30:34.58,0:30:37.50,English,,0,0,0,,It's been great having a sex toy, but\N{\rChinese}拥有性玩具真不错，
Dialogue: 0,0:30:37.50,0:30:40.54,English,,0,0,0,,the gods insist that you have to go home.\N{\rChinese}但众神坚持你必须回家。
Dialogue: 0,0:30:40.64,0:30:45.38,English,,0,0,0,,But you know what? You can choose to be my sex toy for all of eternity.\N{\rChinese}但你知道吗？你可以选择成为我永恒的性玩具。
Dialogue: 0,0:30:45.70,0:30:47.32,English,,0,0,0,,I can make you immortal, right?\N{\rChinese}我可以让你变成不朽的存在，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:30:47.40,0:30:50.38,English,,0,0,0,,You can go home, but I can make you immortal, and you'll be my sex toy for all of eternity.\N{\rChinese}你可以回家，但我能让你变成不朽的存在，你将成为我永恒的性玩具。
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.70,0:30:53.54,English,,0,0,0,,Now, this is like, that's a really nice offer.\N{\rChinese}现在，这就像是个很好的提议。
Dialogue: 0,0:30:53.94,0:30:55.64,English,,0,0,0,,I really want to do this.\N{\rChinese}我真的想做这件事。
Dialogue: 0,0:30:55.64,0:30:57.10,English,,0,0,0,,But I need to go home, okay?\N{\rChinese}我需要回家，好吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:30:57.20,0:31:00.66,English,,0,0,0,,So, he leaves, and he gets on an island.\N{\rChinese}于是他离开，随后抵达一座小岛。
Dialogue: 0,0:31:02.08,0:31:06.16,English,,0,0,0,,And on this island, he's given a ship to go home, okay?\N{\rChinese}在这座岛上，他得到了一艘船去回家，好吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:31:06.22,0:31:08.98,English,,0,0,0,,But before he goes home, as a custom,\N{\rChinese}但在他回家之前，按惯例，
Dialogue: 0,0:31:09.20,0:31:12.60,English,,0,0,0,,they host a banquet for him, okay?\N{\rChinese}他们为他举办了一场宴会，好吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:31:12.74,0:31:14.64,English,,0,0,0,,And they really don't know who he is.\N{\rChinese}他们真的不知道他是谁。
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.78,0:31:17.66,English,,0,0,0,,They don't really know he's Odysseus.\N{\rChinese}他们还没完全知道他是奥德修斯。
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.98,0:31:20.98,English,,0,0,0,,All right? So, during the banquet,\N{\rChinese}好的？于是在宴会上，传统是举行舞会，酒吧演唱一段大事记，好吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:31:23.70,0:31:27.94,English,,0,0,0,,the tradition is to have a ball, and the bar sings a great story, okay?\N{\rChinese}the tradition is to have a ball, and the bar sings a great story, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.00,0:31:31.32,English,,0,0,0,,To sing a story of great deeds.\N{\rChinese}唱响伟业的故事。
Dialogue: 0,0:31:31.56,0:31:34.04,English,,0,0,0,,And of course, he sings about the Trojan War, okay?\N{\rChinese}当然，他在唱歌时提到了特洛伊战争，好吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:31:34.32,0:31:36.88,English,,0,0,0,,So, can you read, Avery?\N{\rChinese}那么，你能读出来吗，艾弗里？
Dialogue: 0,0:31:37.02,0:31:41.40,English,,0,0,0,,Yeah. The Strife Between Odysseus and Achilles, Peleus' son.\N{\rChinese}是的。奥德修斯与阿基琉斯、佩勒斯之子之间的争斗。
Dialogue: 0,0:31:41.52,0:31:44.20,English,,0,0,0,,Okay, so the bar is singing about the Trojan War, okay?\N{\rChinese}好的，酒吧在唱歌时提到了特洛伊战争，好吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:31:44.84,0:31:47.04,English,,0,0,0,,How once at the gods' flowing feast,\N{\rChinese}曾经在众神的盛宴中，
Dialogue: 0,0:31:47.18,0:31:50.38,English,,0,0,0,,the captains clashed in the savage war of wards, while\N{\rChinese}船长们在激烈的守卫战中交锋，随后
Dialogue: 0,0:31:50.38,0:31:53.78,English,,0,0,0,,Agamemnon, lord of armies, rejoiced at heart\N{\rChinese}阿加美农，军队之主，心中喜悦
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.78,0:31:56.20,English,,0,0,0,,that Achilles' bravest men, were battling so.\N{\rChinese}那时，阿基琉斯最勇敢的战士们正在交战。
Dialogue: 0,0:31:56.62,0:31:59.66,English,,0,0,0,,For this was the victory sign, the Apollo of prophecies,\N{\rChinese}这就是胜利的标志，预言之阿波罗
Dialogue: 0,0:31:59.70,0:32:01.84,English,,0,0,0,,at his shrine in Pitho, when\N{\rChinese}在其毕托神殿，时
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.84,0:32:05.84,English,,0,0,0,,Agamemnon strode across the rocky threshold, asking the oracle for advice.\N{\rChinese}阿加美农踏过岩石门槛，向神谕求助
Dialogue: 0,0:32:06.32,0:32:09.72,English,,0,0,0,,The start of the tidal waves of ruin tumbling down on Troy's\N{\rChinese}特洛伊的毁灭潮汹涌而来
Dialogue: 0,0:32:09.72,0:32:14.50,English,,0,0,0,,and Achilles' forces, both at once, thanks to the will of Zeus, who rules the world.\N{\rChinese}并且阿基琉斯的军队，两者同时，因宙斯之意，宙斯主宙世
Dialogue: 0,0:32:15.34,0:32:17.94,English,,0,0,0,,That was the song the famous harper sang but\N{\rChinese}那是那位著名的哈珀所唱的歌
Dialogue: 0,0:32:17.94,0:32:19.44,English,,0,0,0,,Odysseus,\N{\rChinese}奥德修斯,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:19.48,0:32:22.72,English,,0,0,0,,clutching his flaring sea -blue cape in both powerful hands,\N{\rChinese}抓住那绚蓝海色的披风，双手握紧
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.96,0:32:25.50,English,,0,0,0,,drew it over his head, and buried his handsome face.\N{\rChinese}把它披在头上，掩住俊朗的面容
Dialogue: 0,0:32:25.50,0:32:28.96,English,,0,0,0,,He was a man of the world. He was a man of the world. He was a man of the world. He was a man of the world. He was a man of the world. He was a man of the world. Ashamed, his host might see him shedding tears.\N{\rChinese}他是个世间人。 他是个世间人。 他是个世间人。 他是个世间人。 他是个世间人。 他是个世间人。 他是个世间人。 失意之时，他的主人可见他泪流满面。
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.74,0:32:32.06,English,,0,0,0,,Whenever the rapt bard would pause in the song,\N{\rChinese}每当那狂歌者在歌中停顿时，
Dialogue: 0,0:32:32.24,0:32:34.52,English,,0,0,0,,he'd lift the cape from his head,\N{\rChinese}他把披风从头上掀起，擦去泪水
Dialogue: 0,0:32:34.68,0:32:37.94,English,,0,0,0,,wipe off his tears, and hoisting his double -handed cup,\N{\rChinese}举起双手装满的杯子
Dialogue: 0,0:32:38.16,0:32:39.50,English,,0,0,0,,pour it out to the gods.\N{\rChinese}把它倒给诸神。
Dialogue: 0,0:32:40.40,0:32:44.48,English,,0,0,0,,But soon as the bard would start again, impelled to sing by\N{\rChinese}但很快，歌者又起身，随之而唱。
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.30,0:32:47.80,English,,0,0,0,,Theseus' lords, who reveled in his tale,\N{\rChinese}忒修斯的贵族们，沉醉于他的故事，
Dialogue: 0,0:32:47.98,0:32:51.06,English,,0,0,0,,again Odysseus hid his face and wept.\N{\rChinese}又一次奥德修斯掩面而泪
Dialogue: 0,0:32:51.14,0:32:55.90,English,,0,0,0,,Okay, so this is a great banquet, and the bard's singing about the Trojan War.\N{\rChinese}好的，这是一场盛宴，歌者正唱着特洛伊战争。
Dialogue: 0,0:32:56.36,0:32:59.50,English,,0,0,0,,And at this point you would think that Odysseus would be like, hey, that's me, man.\N{\rChinese}此时你会想，奥德修斯会说：嘿，我就是那个人。
Dialogue: 0,0:32:59.62,0:33:03.44,English,,0,0,0,,He'd be very proud. But instead he cries and he cries, okay?\N{\rChinese}他会非常自豪。但他却哭了，哭了，好吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:33:03.68,0:33:05.80,English,,0,0,0,,This again is trauma, where\N{\rChinese}这又是一场创伤，记忆在他心中积存痛楚。
